

  To install this program, do the following...



./configure
make 
make install (as root)




  Soundtank has the following dependencies...


- ALSA (the Advanded Linux Sound Architecture)
	http://alsa-project.org
	debian package: alsa-base & libasound2-dev


- JACK (Jack Audio Connection Kit)
	http://jackit.sf.net
	debian package: jackd libjack0.80.0-dev


- LIBXML2 (XML File Library)
	http://xmlsoft.org/
	 debian package: libxml2 & libxml2-dev


- other things thare are pretty much standard: 
	libncurses#-dev libpopt-dev libreadline#-dev

